The paper deals with machine learning classification and adversarial attacks, which are common topics in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for robustness in safety-critical systems, which falls under the sub-field of computer security (cs.CR). The use of Gaussian process classifiers and the testing of the method on various datasets suggest that the paper may also fall under the sub-fields of computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
